HEADWORD: Superalimentation
<hw>Su`per*al`i*men*ta"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>The
act of overfeeding, or making one take food in excess of the natural
appetite for it.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

